 gaining the confidence of their commander, Holofernes, and cutting off his head while he is asleep; without their commander, the Assyrians are duly routed. This has been a perennially popular Jewish name. In the English-speaking world it was taken up in the 16th century, having been in occasional use among Gentiles before this: for example, it was borne by a niece of William the Conqueror. It enjoyed great popularity between the 1940s and the 1960s. Today's notable bearers include the American novelist  Judith Krantz  (  b. 1928 ) and the Scottish composer  Judith Weir  (  b. 1954 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Judith married Robert de Buci before 1079, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1030–Male":"1030–Surnud","1079–1154":"1079–1154","–Female":"Surnud","before 1079":"enne 1079","1079":"1079","1154":"1154","1030":"1030","about 1075":"7. jaanuar 1079 kuni 6. jaanuar 1080","Europe":"Europe","Drayton Bassett, Staffordshire, England.":"Annandale District, Dumfriesshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1030–Male":"1030–Kuollut","1079–1154":"1079–1154","–Female":"Kuollut","before 1079":"ennen vuotta 1079","1079":"1079","1154":"1154","1030":"1030","about 1075":"vuodesta 7. tammikuuta 1079 vuoteen 6. tammikuuta 1080","Europe":"Europe","Drayton Bassett, Staffordshire, England.":"Annandale District, Dumfriesshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1030–Male":"1030–Décédé","1079–1154":"1079–1154","–Female":"Décédée","before 1079":"avant 1079","1079":"1079","1154":"1154","1030":"1030","about 1075":"du 7 janvier 1079 au 6 janvier 1080","Europe":"Europe","Drayton Bassett, Staffordshire, England.":"Annandale District, Dumfriesshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Judith a épousé Robert de Buci avant 1079, à Europe. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1030–Male":"1030–Verstorben","1079–1154":"1079–1154","–Female":"Verstorben","before 1079":"vor 1079","1079":"1079","115